    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Little Princess</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Yvonne Jimenez letter on July 9 Lives column scores Dotti-Dawn Stevens' parents for turning girl into grotesque caricature of grown woman in order to help her overcome shyness$</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>How on earth can any parent believe that turning their little girl into a grotesque caricature of a grown woman (Lives, July 9) is the way to help her overcome shyness? Dotti-Dawn's referring to herself in the third person is weird. Her denying her tiredness by identifying it as grouchiness reminds me of those girls who deny what they know in order to protect their abusers.</p>
        <p>Yvonne Jimenez  New York</p>
      </block>
